      • withInput

        public <I> Node.NodeBuilder9<A,B,C,D,E,F,G,H,I> withInput(Class<I> input)
        Adds the ninth input to this node. The input is a required, synchronous input of the given type and is bound to a value when the graph is executed.

        The input is associated with an unqualified input key. This is the same as the following:
        builder.withInput(Key.of(input));

        Parameters:
        input - the type of the input
        Returns:
        a node builder that can be used to add additional inputs or define the node's operation
